Fibrate drugs are segmented by type, application, and end-user. In terms of type, the market is categorized into Gemfibrozil, Fenofibrate, Bezafibrate, and others. Among these, Fenofibrate is expected to dominate the market due to its effectiveness in lowering cholesterol and reducing the risk of cardiovascular diseases. When it comes to applications, the market is segmented into cardiovascular disease, metabolic syndrome, hypertriglyceridemia, and others. The increasing prevalence of cardiovascular diseases is driving the growth of the fibrate drugs market, especially in regions with unhealthy eating habits and sedentary lifestyles. Lastly, based on end-user, the market is segmented into hospitals, clinics, ambulatory surgical centers, and others. Hospitals are likely to be the major end-users of fibrate drugs due to the high incidence of cardiovascular diseases and the availability of specialized healthcare professionals for treatment.

